    "created_at": "2012-08-29T20:52:30Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-08-29T20:52:30Z",
    "body": "Solvable either by re-probing for `--help` in the `err` branch, or probing for `--help` first before doing the probe with a required option. Or by making the required non-required and handling its absence later on in your startup logic.\n\nGetopts can only write so much of a program for you. I can't think of any non-elaborate way of making this work automatically otherwise, so closing. LMK if you think this is a mistake, or have a suggestion for how the interface could change to do what you want easily.\n",
